# Performance flags for fastKar's C++ sources.
#
# The tight inner loops in traverse_graph_v2_cpp, traverse_graph_v2_batch_cpp,
# and hash_karyotype_cpp depend on the compiler vectorising array indexing
# and inlining lambda helpers. On environments whose default CXXFLAGS are
# just `-O2` (no SIMD target), the new path can lose most of its advantage
# over the legacy R/data.table path -- empirically observed on R 4.3 with
# a vanilla CRAN build.
#
# `-march=native` produces a binary tuned to the build machine's CPU. If you
# need a portable .so (e.g. you build on one node and deploy to another with
# different SIMD capabilities), replace it with `-march=x86-64-v3` for AVX2
# baseline compatibility, or `-march=haswell` for the equivalent.

PKG_CXXFLAGS = -march=native -ftree-vectorize -fno-math-errno
